{
  "stem": "7455.8",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And when there all I walked into Witzhelden, that small town-- that small town there, from the window we saw German soldiers throwing off in a cemetery, throwing off their uniforms.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the Germans running out and giving them civilian clothes, that they shouldn't be taken prisoner.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then when I looked out from the garage door, I saw German soldiers and I like-- maybe American or-- it was American or English, on the-- with their rifles, leading the Germans hands up, leading them through the road.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My woman, the lady that I worked for, she cried and wept because her husband was in the army, too.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she embraced me, Paula, Fraulein Paula, what's going to be?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How different were our tears.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I cried because it was too late for my parents, too late for Muno, too late for Zigi, too late for Laura, for Rosa.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They dreamed-- my father used to say, I just want to see the Germany capitulated, and then I may die.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't see that moment where the Germans, with their hands up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were-- then they placed an order-- there was in order that the Germans from this side have to cross the road and take a co-- take up-- go into their neighbor's house.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They have to leave their homes because the American, the Allies, they will take over those apartments.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They need quarters to stay.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then she, in the last minute, she wanted to get her preserves and get things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I hear a German-- American soldier say, [SPEAKING YIDDISH.] I realized he was an American soldier speaking Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was too soon for me to reveal myself, who I am.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I know he's a Yiddish, a Jewish soldier.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
